(2, 'Creative Strategies Associate', '<p><p>Reporting to the Creative Strategies Manager, the Creative Strategies Associate will help develop, coordinate, and execute communications activities and initiatives for the Indivisible Project with a focus on design. This person would also assist with broader team-wide tasks, including maintaining and updating content on Indivisible websites, providing photo/video coverage of events, as well as any other projects as assigned.</p> <p>We are hiring for this position immediately. This position is full-time, with a salary range of $40,000-$50,000, commensurate with experience. Indivisible provides a robust benefits package including full medical/dental/vision/life coverage, a discounted gym membership, and a 401(k) plan.</p> <h3><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></h3> <p>Design/Content Creation:</p> <ul> <li>Work with internal and external stakeholders to transform written work and data into compelling visuals</li> <li>Help develop and implement the visual identity of Indivisible Project campaigns;Create, produce, and/or acquire assets including infographics, illustrations, video, still images, and audio</li> <li>Provide photo and video coverage of events, panels, and projects</li> <li>Provide support for weekly livestreams</li> </ul> <p>Other Communications Support:</p> <ul> <li>Support and facilitate coordination for campaigns across teams and with outside stakeholders</li> <li>Help maintain Indivisible.org and other Indivisible Project campaign sites</li> <li>Assist as needed with digital, writing, research, and organizational projects on discrete issue-related and electoral campaigns</li> <li>Other duties as assigned</li> </ul> <h3><strong>Qualifications:</strong></h3> <ul> <li>One to three years of related experience in a professional or volunteer capacity</li> <li>Proficiency with Google Docs, Sheets, and Slides</li> <li>Proficiency with Adobe Creative Suite (Illustrator, InDesign, Photoshop)</li> <li>Competency in basic HTML and CSS and/or experience maintaining web content through a CMS</li> <li>Experience coordinating project deliverables across teams and with outside stakeholders</li> <li>Excellent communication skills—Spanish language skills a plus</li> <li>Demonstrated ability to excel in a fast-paced, campaign-like environment</li> <li>Motivation and willingness to learn</li> <li>Alignment on the core values and strategy of the Indivisible Project</li> </ul> <p>Note: If you believe you can fulfill the job responsibilities, are a good match, and are excited by the position, but do not meet all of the qualifications listed above please still apply and emphasize any transferable skills in your resume. </p></p>', '2017-11-17 14:20:16', 0, '3', 'Indivisible Project', 1, 'Indivisible Project', 'https://www.indivisible.org/', 'Washington, DC, US', 'https://d2fcz5no062gar.cloudfront.net/assets/images/defaults/company-blank.png', 'https://jobs.lever.co/indivisible/3dd1a7e0-da91-418e-b086-5972d1ce76fd?lever-origin=applied&lever-source%5B%5D=AuthenticJobs', 'https://authenticjobs.com/jobs/30037/creative-strategies-associate', NULL, 0, 6);
